 Name:         LIST, display contents of an ASCII file.

 Syntax:       LIST  <[d:][path]filename[.ext]>

 Input:
	An ASCII file of any size may be listed, HOWEVER only the
	first 79 bytes of each record is displayed.

	At any time during the display:

	- Esc	>	>	>  terminate

	- #     (a number)	>  jump a % into a file
                                >  0=Home  5=50% into the file

	- P     (or p)	>       >  toggle printing

	- Home	>	>	>  re-start from beginning
	- End	>	>	>  go to the end of the file

	- U     (or u)	>       >  back up two pages
	- D     (or d)	>       >  advance two pages

	- -     >       >       >  back up 1/2 page
	- +	>	>	>  advance 1/2 page

	- Up	>	>	>  back up one line
	- Dn	>	>	>  advance one line

	- PgUp  >       >       >  display previous frame
	- PgDn (or any other key)  continue to next page

	- Scroll Lock	>       >  toggle scrolling
                                   Up, Dn changes direction
                                   # (0-9) changes speed

 Output:

